column5: Here's a few pics of my outing on Wednesday out on GBay.  Out trolling:    Success, My Believer made a Believer outta me......    Hanging out while I get ready for the successful release, she just swam off calmly....    All in all, a successful day, searching out and finding a couple of reefs that I have wanted to try out.
oh wow thats a nice one - how long?
I figure about 38-40" or so. I didn't have a tape measure with me. Besides, I was fishing by myself so I didn't want to keep the fish out of water for too long.
nice going  I have tried on GB a few times this year and have not a bit of muskie slime anywhere..I will keep trying
Hey.. I know that spot! lol  Nice one Buck !
Nice Fish.  I troll with the Believer quite a bit and have never even had a hit on one yet. I know other who use them - with success. Congrats.
Joey, it's not snow, it's rain that must have reflected the flash, it was getting pretty dark when I caught the fish.
Nice healthy GB Ski. That's the best time to catch a Musky! Before the storm, during or in between breaks! Thanks for sharing.
Looks like a successful excursion. Picked your spot and sure enough there was a decent muskie waiting for you. Very nice
